# I/O, Input, View & App

## Stdin protocol (do not change without explicit request)

1. Board rows until `Board:` marker (or legacy: rows then `Commands:`)
2. Commands: `click X Y`, `jump X Y`, `wait MS`, `print board`
3. Errors to stdout: `ERROR UNKNOWN_TOKEN`, `ERROR ROW_WIDTH_MISMATCH`, etc.
4. `main.cpp` runs the whole protocol via `ScriptRunner::run(std::cin, std::cout)` — no hardcoded demo

## Layer roles

| Layer | Does | Does not |
|-------|------|----------|
| `io/` | Parse/print board text | Validate moves |
| `input/` | Map pixels/clicks → `Position` | Hold game state |
| `view/` | Render `GameSnapshot` | Mutate `Board` |
| `App` | Wire engine + I/O + input + view | Implement piece rules |

## Input flow

```
stdin → ScriptParser → ScriptRunner → Controller → GameEngine → snapshot → BoardPrinter
```

- `BoardMapper`: pixel `(x, y)` → grid `Position` using cell size constant
- `Controller`: translate `click` into `requestMove(from, to)` based on selection state (clicking another
  same-color piece re-targets the selection instead of requesting a move); translate `jump` directly into
  `requestJump(at)`
- `ScriptParser`: parses the `Board:`/`Commands:` protocol into a `Board` + `ScriptCommand` list
- `ScriptRunner`: replays parsed commands against a fresh `GameEngine`/`Controller`, writing `print board`
  output; this is what `main.cpp` calls with `std::cin`/`std::cout`

## View flow

- Receive `GameSnapshot` const reference or value copy
- No direct `Board` access; all display data comes from the snapshot DTO
- Keep rendering logic free of rule checks
